  "decision_conditions": [
    "Reason : 1 - In the absence of the provision of required off-street parking and/or parking survey to demonstrate there is capacity in the locality to accommodate the parking demand arising from the proposed development, the scheme is considered to adversely impact on the free flow of traffic in the locality to the detriment of highway and pedestrian safety.  The proposal is contrary to, in particular, Merton's Core Strategy (2011) Policy CS 20, Merton's Sites and Policies Plan (2014) policy DM T2 and London Plan policies T5 and T6.1.",
    "Reason : 2 - By reason of lack of provision of accessible, secure and weatherproof cycle parking provision, the scheme fails to promote sustainable form of travel, contrary to the aims and objectives set out in, in particular, London Plan Policies T5 and T6.1 and Merton Core Strategy (2011) Policy CS18.",
    "Reason : 3 - The scheme, by reason of absence of details of refuse & recycling stores, the scheme would adversely impact on the visual amenity of the locality and the free flow of traffic and pedestrian and vehicular safety on the surrounding roads.  The scheme fails to comply with, in particular, Policy T6 of the London Plan and Policy CS.19 of the Merton Core Planning Strategy 2011 and Merton Sites and Policies Plan 2014 DM D2.",
    "Reason : 4 - By reason of siting, layout, the introduction of north facing single aspect units and absence of a daylight/sunlight assessment to confirm the provision of adequate natural light in all habitable rooms of the flats, in particular Flats 3 and 4, the scheme represents over-intensification and over-development of the site that would result in sub-standard living conditions and environment, to the detriment of the amenities of future occupiers.  The development would thereby be contrary to, in particular, policy DM D2 of Merton Sites and Policies Plan (2014) and policy D6 of the London Plan 2021."
  ],
